<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest  is called '<span class="yellow">Frost Mages</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">120</span> to <span class="yellow">180</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/388">Lord Telleri</a> [<a href="/area/56">Tellerium</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

News of the powerful magic being harnessed at the Frost Giant's Keep and<br />
Templeton to the north causes me great concern.  Though a stong anti-magic<br />
field protects Tellerium, if these mages of the north become too powerful<br />
they may decide to attempt to destroy this protection that has made<br />
Tellerium home to warriors of all types during their training without fear<br />
of interference by magicians and their tricks.  Therefore, you are to seek<br />
out and destroy these materials that they are using as well as the one who<br />
is organizing this effort.  You will be well rewarded if you are successful.<br />
May the Powers light your steps!<br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">42</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">4</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">30,000</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">8,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">300</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Frost Mages consists of:<br />


